<br>
There's been lots of changes to PVP in the last year and a half, but there seems to be a few relatively recent (like the last six months) changes that allow for certain classes to make pets go poof in PVP and I'm trying to get a handle on exactly which classes can do it, and how it's done. Very often I'm in a multigroup pvp battle and I can't dig through the battle spam to figure out how it was always done.<br>
<br>
The first one I've always known about is Bard charm. A bard can charm your pet (3 second cast), but it won't actually &quot;charm&quot; the pet. Once the charm song effect would end (the &quot;song wears off&quot;) the pet poofs. It's a 12 second effect, so within 15 seconds your pet is gone.<br>
<br>
I believe chanters can do a similar thing by charming the pet (again, it doesn't really take effect), and then dispelling their own charm. Not positive though.<br>
<br>
Now, there are other classes that are able to poof the pet in some way with either a pummice (old-school egg shaped I think) or annul/dispell but they do it not by dispelling the pet, but dispelling the target (often themselves). I'm not clear on the details but if anyone knows, I'd love to learn more.<br>
<br>
Any help at all would be appreciated. <p><font color=blue><i><b>Svenuce Summonstuff</b></i></font><br>
56th Conjurer<br>
Resident of The Last Humble House<br>
Holder of 24 of 28 epic components<br>
<b>Wants to buy or trade for Rage of Zomm</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugyminifireheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GyminiFireheart </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333333>(4/24/01 4:08:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PVP Pet Poofing...</span><hr size=1> pet poofing can be done on blue servers not sure about yours by any class that can blind/fear if your pet is &quot;feared&quot; (or blinded) and it goes out of range (not exactly sure what exact distance) it will poof.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uezno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ezno</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/posticons/eyes.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 414<br> <font color=#333333>(4/24/01 4:19:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PVP Pet Poofing...</span><hr size=1> <br>
I haven't had any pets &quot;poof&quot;.  I have had pets go rogue because of the old pumice bug but as far as I know that was fixed.  I've nullified my pets target before to get rid of sow and haven't had any problems with my pet.  (This used to make the pet go rogue).  <br>
<br>
I've had my pet feared and run off quite a distance and never had it poof, though I've almost wished it were so when I see &quot;taunting attacker master&quot;  a minute later.<br>
<br>
If you find out anything let me know.  I'd be interested in checking it out and seeing how it works. <p> <br>
<b>Ez</b> <br>
<i>"Good... Bad... I'm the guy with the fire elemental."</i><br><i>"Shop Smart. Shop Ez-Mart!"</i><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugyminifireheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GyminiFireheart </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#333333>(4/24/01 6:10:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PVP Pet Poofing...</span><hr size=1> Ezno my pet has personally poofed twice cause of that not sure exact distance because I was busy fighintg but I've had it happen with a shaman (blind) and sk (fear) so I KNOW it poofs from distance, try it again you may get diff results <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucaud12p.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caud12p</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#333333>(4/24/01 7:40:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PVP Pet Poofing...</span><hr size=1> The pet poofs most often when annuling someone that the pet is attacking, a PC.  I have never been able to clearly identify why this happens, since it is very random.  The best strategy is to always calm down pet 1 second before pumicing someone, then sending pet back in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uezno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ezno</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/posticons/eyes.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 415<br> <font color=#333333>(4/24/01 3:21:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PVP Pet Poofing...</span><hr size=1> <br>
I'll have to give it a try and see what happens.   I remember nullifying my pets target about a month or so ago and had no problems with it.  Actually got lucky and got rid of SoW but the shaman I was fighting had that clickable SoW item and just reapplied.  Arg.  <br>
<br>
I can't remember the last time my pet was feared and I didn't follow it.  If I'm solo I will sometimes follow the pet unless in dangerous territory or fighting an opponent that I don't need the pet for (I like following the pet vs necros unless their petless).   <br>
<br>
I'm not saying your pets aren't poofing, I'm saying i've never had it happen or heard of it.  I'm pretty active on Tallon Zek's msg board and no posts there about it.  I would assume its relatively recent because of that.  I haven't been playing as much lately (and when I do I play an alt more than my main).  Might be something with one of the recent patches.  <br>
<br>
If I get a chance I'll try and experiment with it a little bit. <p> <br>
<b>Ez</b> <br>
<i>"Good... Bad... I'm the guy with the fire elemental."</i><br><i>"Shop Smart. Shop Ez-Mart!"</i><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uyellishen2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yellishen2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(4/25/01 7:39:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PVP Pet Poofing...</span><hr size=1> Yep I've been seeing this problem when your pet is actively engaged on a targe, and within melee range.  If you cast annul on your target, sometimes the pet will poof.  It seems to be random though.  It happens with the epic pet too.  It's a shock from knowing you're going to own somebody to suddenly having to run because of some bug causing your pet to go poof.<br>
<br>
I would agree that backing your pet off 1 second prior to the spell landing seems to work. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utrezark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trezark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(5/8/01 4:26:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PVP Pet Poofing...</span><hr size=1> I dunno if this has anything to do with the poofing problem here, but I've been told that in a PvP situation, if you do anything at all to aggro your pet (i.e. somehow manage to make it on to your pet's hate list), it will kill itself.  I've experimented with this myself, and I seem to recall casting a DD on my pet once in an arena and having him die.<br>
<br>
Now I'm not entirely sure if dispelling a target that your pet is attacking is grounds for it to get annoyed at you, but I suppose it's a possibility.  Maybe the pet sees the cancel as a benevolent spell and thus gets mad at you for helping its target?  I don't see how, since casting cancel on a mob will aggro it, but maybe these things are more complicated than they seem... <p><BR><CENTER><hr size=1 WIDTH=75%>
<font face=arial size=-2>[45 Magician] <A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=57050">Trezark S`Dious</A> (Dark Elf) &lt;<A HREF="http://www.black-reign.net">Black Reign</A>&gt; SERVER: Vazaelle<BR><i>"You could no more evade my wrath than you could your own shadow..."</i></FONT></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ularanos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laranos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(5/13/01 10:54:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PVP Pet Poofing...</span><hr size=1> Ok, here's the skinny. Instead of dealing with rogue pets, VI coded it so that -anything- that would make your pet go rogue poofs the pet. In the arena this means if you hit it with a bolt...if you annull a target with an empty buff slot, it goes rogue, and poofs. If a bard charms it and lets it go, it poofs, etc. etc. etc. I have done a -lot- of experimenting with this stuff. Basically, rather then just -fix- the problems associated with pets going rogue, they decided to make pets poof into non-existance instead. Basically, that means we are unable to use an entire spell line in pvp because it might poof our pet, bards get a free manaless kill on our pets, and enchanters basically get to screw us. Absor was once quoted as saying that a mage's pet is 50% of their power...well, for pvp, eliminating that 50% is as easy as shooting fish in a barrel.<br>
<br>
Laranos Lostpuddle, Level 55 Gnomish Magi of Tallon Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showPrevMessage?topicID=22.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showNextMessage?topicID=22.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.threadControl?topicID=22.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<option value="themagicianstowerspells">Spells<option value="themagicianstowerequipmentandquests">Quests<option value="themagicianstowerfrm28">Equipment<option value="themagicianstowerfrm29">Magician Pets<option value